# Engineering Playbook ([PROJECT_NAME])

Read when: implementing, testing, validating, or troubleshooting.
Skip when: never.

Single source for commands, testing policy, feature execution, and repository structure.

## 1) Commands
```bash
# setup
[SETUP_COMMANDS]

# run/build
[BUILD_RUN_COMMAND]
[LOCAL_ONLY_RUN_COMMAND]

# logs/troubleshooting
[LOGS_COMMAND]

# quality
[LINT_COMMAND]
[FORMAT_CHECK_COMMAND]
[TYPECHECK_COMMAND]

# tests
[SMOKE_COMMAND]
[TARGETED_TEST_COMMAND]
[COVERAGE_COMMAND]

# full validation gate
[VERIFY_COMMAND]
```

## 2) Test Policy
- Every behavior change maps to at least one targeted test.
- Smoke tests remain fast and run in seconds.
- Verify gate is mandatory before handoff.

## 2.2) Branching and PR Workflow
- Branching model: [TRUNK_BASED_OR_GITFLOW]
- Branch naming: `[feature|fix|chore]/[short-description]`
- PR size target: [SMALL_MEDIUM]
- Merge rule: [SQUASH_OR_MERGE_COMMIT]
- Required checks before merge: verify gate + CI + required reviewers

## 2.3) Code Review Guidelines
- Review for correctness, security impact, test coverage, and rollback safety.
- Reject undocumented behavior changes.
- Require at least one approver for Tier A and two for Tier B/C (or document solo-owner exception).
- Ensure commands/docs/paths changed in code are updated in docs in the same change.

## 2.1) Manual Smoke Runbook (Concise)
1. Start app/runtime.
2. Initialize data store if needed.
3. Create bootstrap/admin user if needed.
4. Validate auth, core workflow, and logout manually.
5. Run `[SMOKE_COMMAND]`, `[TARGETED_TEST_COMMAND]`, and `[VERIFY_COMMAND]`.

## 3) Workflow-to-Test Matrix
| Workflow | Command | Type | Required by Tier |
|---|---|---|---|
| Syntax/build integrity | `[SYNTAX_COMMAND]` | static/smoke | A/B/C |
| Startup/load integrity | `[SMOKE_COMMAND]` | smoke | A/B/C |
| Core workflow behavior | `[TARGETED_TEST_COMMAND]` | targeted | A/B/C |
| Full local validation | `[VERIFY_COMMAND]` | gate | A/B/C |
| Coverage confidence | `[COVERAGE_COMMAND]` | regression | B/C |

